If $n=1$,
$$
E_1=-2.178 \times 10^{-18} Z^2 \mathrm{~J}
$$
If $n=6$
$$
\begin{aligned}
E_6 & =\frac{-2.178 \times 10^{-18} Z^2}{36} \mathrm{~J} \\
& =6.05 \times 10^{-20} Z^2 \mathrm{~J}
\end{aligned}
$$
From the above calculation, it is abvious that electron has a more negative energy than it does for $n=6$. It means that electron is more strongly bound in the smallest allowed orbit.
